WEBVTT

00:00.899 --> 00:05.600
ï»¿The darker side of chocolate has some surprising health benefits.

00:07.071 --> 00:09.061
Its impressive antioxidant powers...

00:09.183 --> 00:11.968
...fight free radicals better than almost any other food,...

00:12.274 --> 00:14.302
...almost eight times that of a strawberry.

00:14.685 --> 00:17.891
These same flavanols can stimulate the lining of arteries,...

00:18.203 --> 00:21.913
...allowing them to relax and increase blood flow and reduce blood pressure.

00:22.375 --> 00:26.743
It can also inhibit bad cholesterol and increases your good cholesterol, HDL...

00:26.911 --> 00:29.443
...and can help prevent heart disease and diabetes.

00:29.679 --> 00:32.615
A one ounce serving size of delicious dark chocolate...

00:32.924 --> 00:36.377
...has a surprising amount of fiber, vitamins and minerals.

00:36.953 --> 00:41.053
The bioactive compounds of dark chocolate may also protect against sun damage,...

00:41.288 --> 00:45.207
...improve blood flow to the skin, increase skin density and hydration.

00:45.571 --> 00:49.078
In one study, it doubled the body's tolerance to sun exposure.

00:49.604 --> 00:52.312
While these health benefits are certainly very exciting,...

00:52.498 --> 00:54.415
...it's important to keep things in moderation.

00:54.749 --> 00:58.493
Savoring a small one-inch piece of high quality dark chocolate per night...

00:58.689 --> 00:59.611
...is probably about right.

00:59.837 --> 01:04.419
And remember that you should be aiming for over 70% cacao in your dark chocolate.

01:04.639 --> 01:06.643
And the higher the percentage, the better.

